  "text": "The ECM in blood vessels contains coll I and coll III. Whereas coll III is quantitatively more important during fetal development, coll I is more abundant in the adult. The organic matrix of a plaque also consists mainly of coll I and coll III [CITATION_1] . Therefore the distribution and density of these two types of collagen was studied.",
